# Soča Guide — Deployment & Safety Rules

## Deployment Context

- **Production** is live on **Vercel** via the **`Vujos1` branch**
- Every push to `Vujos1` deploys to production — treat all changes as production-grade
- **Do NOT push to `main`** without explicit user confirmation

## Patch Safety Rules

- **DO NOT change build structure** — no new folders at root, no changes to `vercel.json`, `package.json`, or any config files
- **DO NOT change root files** — `index.html`, `sw.js` and other root-level files are sensitive; only patch them when the user explicitly requests it
- **SAFE PATCH only** — surgical, minimal edits; never refactor working code unless asked
- Always bump JS/CSS version query strings (e.g. `?v=YYYYMMDD-N`) when editing cached assets so Vercel CDN invalidates correctly
- Never rename or move files that are referenced by existing HTML `<script src>` or `<link href>` tags

## Tech Stack Reminder

- Static site (no build step) — plain HTML + vanilla JS
- Supabase (Postgres + Storage + Edge Functions + Auth)
- Resend for transactional email via Edge Function `send-email`
- No npm, no bundler, no framework
